article.description: Bryce Moore scored 13 of his 16 points in the second half and Western Michigan beat Miami (Ohio) 67-62 on Saturday for its fourth straight victory.
article.headline: Western Michigan rallies to beat Miami (OH) 67-62
article.linkText: Western Michigan rallies to beat Miami (OH) 67-62
article.story: OXFORD, Ohio -- Bryce Moore scored 13 of his 16 points in the second half and Western Michigan beat Miami (Ohio) 67-62 on Saturday for its fourth straight victory. Thomas Wilder added 13 points and Josh Davis scored 10 and grabbed 11 rebounds for the Broncos (10-5, 2-0 Mid-American Conference), who scored 16 points off of 13 RedHawks' turnovers. Western Michigan trailed by 12 points early in the second half but took the lead, 57-56, amid a 21-3 run. The RedHawks got within 65-62 on Darrian Ringo's layup with 13 seconds left, but Brandon Johnson dunked it on the other end. Miami led 33-27 at halftime after holding the Broncos to 35.5 percent shooting from the floor. Ringo scored 14 points with 11 rebounds and Mike Sibande added 13 points for the RedHawks (8-7, 1-1).
